{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.15.1515;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\b\f0\fs20 Sometimes the database you are using might generate an error.\par
\par
You can capture these using an Error event. The Error event can capture a specific kind of error, or, you can use the Any Event type to handle any error not handled by a lower-level handler.\par
\par
In this example, any error triggers a generic screen giving data about the error. This screen uses some Magic functions you might fine useful. You can log this information to keep track of errors not reported by the users.\par
\par
Try creating two records with the same record ID, to trigger an error.\par
